# System Patterns

## Repository Architecture

```
My-enterprise-app/
├── .cursor/
│   ├── rules/
│   │   └── global_standards/       # Common standards everyone follows
│   │       ├── product_context.mdc
│   │       ├── tech_context.mdc
│   │       ├── system_patterns.mdc
│   │       └── design_system.mdc
│   └── skills/                     # Agent skill definitions
│       ├── write-bsr/SKILL.md
│       ├── write-test-cases/SKILL.md
│       └── write-context-sensitive-help/SKILL.md
│
├── base/                           # Shared / legacy application shell
│   └── dev/
│       └── src/                    # Vite React app entry (main.tsx, App shell)
│
├── features/
│   ├── Feature-1/
│   │   ├── ba/                     # Business Analysis workspace
│   │   │   ├── AGENTS.md
│   │   │   ├── req_context.md      # Living log of requirements prompt steps
│   │   │   └── req/                # BSR, mockups, mock data
│   │   ├── dev/                    # Development workspace
│   │   │   ├── AGENTS.md
│   │   │   ├── src_context.md      # Living log of code prompt steps
│   │   │   └── src/                # Production source code
│   │   ├── qc/                     # Quality Control workspace
│   │   │   ├── AGENTS.md
│   │   │   ├── test_context.md     # Living log of test prompt steps
│   │   │   └── test/               # Test cases, data, automation scripts
│   │   └── idg/                    # Information Development Group workspace
│   │       ├── AGENTS.md
│   │       ├── docs_context.md     # Living log of documentation prompt steps
│   │       └── docs/               # Release notes, online help, manuals
│   ├── Feature-2/
│   └── Feature-N/
```

### Base application shell (`base/`)

- **`base/dev/src/`** is the Vite React application entry (legacy / shared shell). There is no root `src/` folder.
- New feature work still lands in `features/Feature-N/dev/src/` and is composed into the shell as features mature.
- Vite entry: `index.html` → `/base/dev/src/main.tsx`; path alias `@` → `base/dev/src`.

## Agent write boundaries (non-negotiable)

Each discipline agent may write **only** inside its own folder (`ba/`, `dev/`, `qc/`, `idg/`).
Cross-folder implementation (route wiring, Vite plugins, app shell) is **Dev** (or explicit human) work.
BA prototypes and temporary wired pages live in `features/*/ba/req/`, not `dev/src/`.

## Multi-Disciplinary Protocol

1. **Context boundary lock**: Each discipline writes exclusively to its own directory
2. **Upstream read access**: Dev reads `ba/`; QC reads both `ba/` and `dev/`; IDG reads both `ba/` and `dev/`
3. **Living Context Loop**: Every agent reads `*_context.md` before work and updates it after every change
4. **Reproducibility goal**: `req/`, `src/`, `test/`, and `docs/` folders must be 100% recreatable from context ledgers

## Naming Conventions

| Artifact | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| BSR document | `FeatureNBSR.md` | `Feature1BSR.md` |
| Page mockup | `FeatureNPageMockup.tsx` | `Feature1PageMockup.tsx` |
| Mock data | `FeatureNMockData.json` | `Feature1MockData.json` |
| Page component | `FeatureNPage.tsx` | `Feature1Page.tsx` |
| Sub-component | `FeatureNWidget.tsx` | `Feature1Widget.tsx` |
| Logic/API/helpers | `FeatureNUtils.ts` | `Feature1Utils.ts` |
| Release notes | `FeatureNReleaseNotes.md` | `Feature1ReleaseNotes.md` |
| Online help | `FeatureNOnlineHelp.md` | `Feature1OnlineHelp.md` |
| Context-sensitive help | `FeatureN-csh.md` | `Feature1-csh.md` |
| User manual | `FeatureNManual.md` | `Feature1Manual.md` |

## Parallel Sprint Rules

1. BA commits to `features/Feature-N/ba/*`
2. Dev pulls BA changes, commits to `features/Feature-N/dev/*`
3. QC pulls both, commits to `features/Feature-N/qc/*`
4. IDG pulls BA and Dev changes, commits to `features/Feature-N/idg/*`
5. Cross-feature dependencies require explicit `@` path tagging

## Agent Configuration Files

Each discipline folder contains an uppercase `AGENTS.md` that defines:
- Context boundary (read/write scope)
- Work product output locations
- Mandatory Living Context Loop requirements
